</it> (in 1986). He also had minor roles in several films, such as <it><movie wordnetid="106613686" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../818/454818.xml">
The Abominable Dr. Phibes</link></movie>
</it> (1971) and <it><movie wordnetid="106613686" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../358/3978358.xml">
The Medusa Touch</link></movie>
</it> (1978).</p>
<p>

Marter was married, and had two sons. He died suddenly at his home in <village wordnetid="108672738" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../867/17867.xml">
London</link></village>
 on his forty-second birthday in 1986, after suffering a <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../969/60969.xml">
heart attack</link> brought on by complications of <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../677/44677.xml">
diabetes</link>. </p>


